# WalletPulse Project Context

## What is WalletPulse?

An Android-first, multi-currency expense tracker built with React Native. It captures push notifications from financial apps (Payoneer, Grey, Dukascopy Bank), parses transaction details through regex, and persists them to a per-user Supabase Postgres database with real-time currency conversion. Designed to compete with top expense trackers through speed, functionality, and a polished enterprise-grade UI.

## Development Philosophy

- **Test-Driven Development (TDD)**: Write failing tests first, then implementation, then refactor
- **Clean Architecture**: Domain, Data, Presentation, and Infrastructure layers with strict dependency rules
- **Enterprise UI**: Human-centered design with micro-interactions, skeleton loading, haptic feedback, and accessibility
- **No em dashes**: Never use the "--" (em dash) character in any text, comments, UI strings, or documentation

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Framework | React Native 0.84 (bare workflow, no Expo) |
| Language | TypeScript (strict mode) |
| Persistence | Supabase Postgres via `@supabase/supabase-js` (per-user rows, scoped by `user_id`) |
| Auth (current) | Custom `users`/`sessions` tables + `react-native-keychain` token storage. NOTE: this predates Supabase Auth and should eventually be migrated. |
| State | Zustand for UI state + manual `useEffect + refetch` hooks for data |
| Navigation | React Navigation 7 (bottom tabs + native stack) |
| Charts | react-native-gifted-charts |
| Styling | React Native StyleSheet + design token system (`src/shared/theme`) |
| Notifications | Android NotificationListenerService (native module) + `@notifee/react-native` for outgoing reminders |
| FX Rates | ExchangeRate-API (free tier) cached in `fx_rates` table |
| Security | `react-native-keychain` for session tokens, PIN lock with `react-native-quick-crypto` |
| Testing | Jest + @testing-library/react-native (TDD) |
| Animations | react-native-reanimated 4 |

**Important**: Earlier docs referenced WatermelonDB. The app does NOT use WatermelonDB. All persistence goes through Supabase. Do not introduce WatermelonDB imports or observables.

## Clean Architecture Structure

```
src/
├── app/                       # App entry + Providers
├── domain/                    # Pure business logic (no framework imports)
│   ├── entities/              # Core business objects
│   ├── repositories/          # Repository interfaces (ports)
│   ├── usecases/              # Application business rules
│   └── value-objects/         # Immutable value types (Money, Currency)
├── data/                      # Data layer (implements domain interfaces)
│   ├── repositories/          # Supabase-backed implementations
│   ├── datasources/           # SupabaseDataSource, RemoteDataSource (FX), supabase-client
│   ├── seed/                  # Default-category / currency seed scripts
│   └── sync/                  # Settings pull/push helpers
├── presentation/              # UI layer
│   ├── screens/               # Full screen components
│   ├── components/            # Reusable UI components
│   ├── navigation/            # React Navigation setup and types
│   ├── stores/                # Zustand stores (presentation state)
│   └── hooks/                 # UI-specific hooks (data fetching, selectors)
├── infrastructure/            # External services and platform code
│   ├── notification/          # Incoming-notification listener, parsers, dedup, orchestrator
│   ├── currency/              # FX service (fetch + cache + convert)
│   ├── recurring/             # Recurring bill/subscription scheduler
│   ├── backup/                # Backup service
│   ├── security/              # PIN + biometric services
│   └── native/                # Native module JS bridges
└── shared/                    # Cross-cutting concerns
    ├── theme/                 # Design tokens (colors, typography, spacing, radius, shadows)
    ├── types/                 # Shared TypeScript types
    ├── utils/                 # Pure utility functions
    └── constants/             # App-wide constants
__tests__/                     # Mirrors src/ structure
```

## Dependency Rule

```
Presentation --> Domain <-- Data
                   ^
                   |
             Infrastructure
```

Domain layer has ZERO imports from any other layer. Data and Infrastructure depend on Domain. Presentation depends on Domain and receives data through hooks/stores.

## Data Access Pattern

- A single `SupabaseDataSource` (see `src/data/datasources/SupabaseDataSource.ts`) exposes typed repositories scoped to the current `userId`.
- Presentation hooks call `getSupabaseDataSource().<repo>.<method>()` inside a `useEffect`, store the result in React state, and re-run via an incrementing `refetchKey`. There are no reactive DB observables.
- Writes always go through a use case in `src/domain/usecases/`; never call `supabase.from(...)` or `repo.save(...)` directly from a component.

## Key Conventions

- All financial amounts stored as integers (cents) to avoid float rounding
- Dates stored as Unix timestamps (milliseconds)
- Currency codes follow ISO 4217 (USD, EUR, GBP, ETB)
- Every Supabase table has `created_at` and `updated_at` columns (milliseconds as `bigint`)
- All queries include `.eq('user_id', this.userId)` in the repository layer
- Notification parsers are pure functions: `(notification) => ParsedTransaction | null`
- Components use named exports, screens use default exports
- File naming: `kebab-case.ts` for logic, `PascalCase.tsx` for components
- Every new module starts with a test file (TDD red-green-refactor)
- Never use em dash characters anywhere in the codebase
